# macRo — env vars consumed by the release flow.
#
# This file is documentation only. Copy values from GitHub Secrets /
# 1Password / Apple Developer Portal — never commit real secrets.
#
# Real values live in:
#   - GitHub Secrets (per repo, Actions workflow only)
#   - 1Password (Sparkle private key, macRo / Sparkle Private Key)
#   - Apple Developer Portal (team ID, app-specific password)
#
# See tools/release/README.md for the four-step bootstrap that uploads
# every secret below to GitHub.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apple Developer ID — for codesigning + notarization (notarize.sh)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Your Apple Developer Apple ID (email). Visible at https://appleid.apple.com.
APPLE_ID=your-developer-apple-id@example.com

# 10-char Apple Developer team ID. Find at
# https://developer.apple.com/account → Membership.
APPLE_TEAM_ID=XXXXXXXXXX

# App-specific password generated at https://appleid.apple.com →
# App-Specific Passwords. NOT your real Apple ID password.
APPLE_NOTARY_PASSWORD=app-specific-password-not-your-real-apple-password

# Exact certificate name as listed in Keychain Access. Includes the
# 10-char team ID in parens at the end.
MACOS_CERTIFICATE_NAME="Developer ID Application: Your Name (XXXXXXXXXX)"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apple Developer ID cert — GitHub Actions only (workflow imports into a
# scratch keychain). Do NOT put real values in any local .env file.
#
# Generate via:  base64 -i cert.p12 | pbcopy
# Upload to:     GitHub Secrets → MACOS_CERTIFICATE / MACOS_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# MACOS_CERTIFICATE=<base64-encoded p12 blob — GitHub Secrets only>
# MACOS_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD=<p12 export passphrase>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sparkle EdDSA private key — for appcast signing in CI
# (generate-appcast.sh).
#
# Generated by Sparkle's generate_keys utility (see
# tools/release/README.md → Bootstrap step 1). Stored in macOS Keychain
# locally; copied to 1Password (macRo / Sparkle Private Key) and uploaded
# to GitHub Secrets as SPARKLE_ED_PRIVATE_KEY.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SPARKLE_ED_PRIVATE_KEY=<raw EdDSA private key blob — GitHub Secrets / 1Password only>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# generate-appcast.sh runtime env (set by GitHub Actions workflow)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# GitHub repo owner/name — workflow sets via ${{ github.repository }}.
# Local override:
# GITHUB_REPO=estevanhernandez-stack-ed/Macro

# GitHub auth for `gh` CLI — workflow sets via ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}.
# Local override:  export GH_TOKEN="$(gh auth token)"
# GH_TOKEN=
